com.ti.debug.engine.scripting

Class ProfileClock

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ti.debug.engine.scripting.ProfileClock

  • public class ProfileClock
extends java.lang.Object
    This class serves as a encapsulates the Port Connect methods (used with supported simulators to allow reading and writing of a file through a memory address). An instance of this class is automatically created when a new debug session is opened.

      • enable

        public void enable()
            throws ScriptingException

        ScriptingException

      • enableAutoreset

        public void enableAutoreset()
        Enable Auto-Reset mode of the Profile Clock. If enabled, the Profile Clock will reset its count each time prior to running the target.
        See Also:
        disableAutoreset()

      • getEventCount

        public int getEventCount()
                  throws ScriptingException
        Get the number of clock events that are configurable on this device. Use this method in combination with getEventName(int) to get the names of all the configurable Profile Clock events.
        Returns:
        Number of Profile Clock events.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • getEventID

        public int getEventID(java.lang.String sEventName)
               throws ScriptingException
        Get the event ID that corresponds to an event name. This method will perform a case-insensitive match of sEventName against all of the Profile Clock events that the current target supports.
        Returns:
        The numeric event ID that corresponds to a particular event name or -1 if no matching event was found.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • getEventName

        public java.lang.String getEventName(int nEventID)
                              throws ScriptingException
        Get the name corresponding to a particular profiling event ID. Note: The event ID is a zero-based index. Valid event IDs range from 0 to (getEventCount() - 1). If nEventID is invalid/out-of-range then a ScriptingException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        nEventID - The zero-base event ID to set
        Returns:
        The name of event corresponding to nEventID
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • setCurrentEvent

        public void setCurrentEvent(int nEventID)
                     throws ScriptingException
        Configures the Profile Clock to profile/count a particular event. The previously accumulated event count is reset to zero (unless nEventID happens to be the already-configured event, in which case no action is performed). Note: The event ID is a zero-based index. Valid event IDs range from 0 to (getEventCount() - 1).
        Parameters:
        nEventID - The zero-base event ID to set
        Throws:
        ScriptingException
